[size=6][b]Station Budget Watchdog[/b][/size]

Keeps player stations with configured name tags funded to a manual target you control, and reclaims their hoarded surplus. It can also bypass the name-tag filter and handle every player station using the vanilla planned budget, reproducing the original HappyStation style. No vanilla files are patched; safe to add to or remove from an existing save.

[size=4][b]Why[/b][/size]

The vanilla "expected operating budget" is calculated from a station's potential cargo volume, so a big warehouse politely asks you to donate more credits than you will gather in the entire playthrough - and then parks whatever it gets as unusable dead weight. A manual per-tag target keeps each station liquid enough to trade while your money keeps working elsewhere.

[size=4][b]Game version compatibility[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][i]9.00 release[/i] - [b]supported[/b][/*]
[*][i]9.00 betas and release candidates[/i] - [b]supported[/b][/*]
[*][i]8.00 release[/i] - [b]supported[/b][/*]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Dependencies[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]SirNukes Mod Support APIs[/b] ([url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/503]link[/url]) - hard dependency; provides the Extension Options menu used for configuration.[/*]
[/list]

[size=4][b]How it works[/b][/size]

Put a tag like [[font=Courier New]QT57][/font] in a station's name and give that tag a target budget [font=Courier New]T[/font]. On every check the watchdog looks at the live balance (default levels shown; all of them are sliders in the options menu):

[list]
[*][font=Courier New]money < 1x T[/font]: grants credits up to the fill level ([font=Courier New]2x T[/font]), capped by your account. If you cannot afford that, it tries the plain deficit (back to [font=Courier New]1x T[/font]); if you cannot afford even that, it warns and waits.[/*]
[*][font=Courier New]money >[/font] trigger level ([font=Courier New]3x T[/font]): reclaims the surplus, leaving the leave level ([font=Courier New]1.5x T[/font]) at the station.[/*]
[*]in between: leaves the station alone.[/*]
[/list]

The wide deadband prevents back-and-forth transfers, and the watchdog clamps the levels at runtime so a fresh top-up can never itself trip the drain.

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

Open Extension Options and use the Station Budget Watchdog menu to add or remove station-name tags and their target budgets, and to tune the watchdog:

[list]
[*][b]Check interval[/b] - default: 30 s. How often all stations are checked.[/*]
[*][b]Minimum transfer[/b] - default: 1 M Cr. Floor for any single grant or drain.[/*]
[*][b]Minimum kept player money[/b] - default: 20 M Cr. Wallet reserve top-ups never dip into.[/*]
[*][b]Top-up fill level[/b] - default: 200 %. Balance a grant fills up to, in percent of target.[/*]
[*][b]Drain trigger level[/b] - default: 300 %. Balance above which surplus is reclaimed.[/*]
[*][b]Drain leave level[/b] - default: 150 %. Balance a drain leaves at the station.[/*]
[/list]

Default tags:

[list]
[*][font=Courier New][AB5][/font] - 5,000,000 Cr[/*]
[*][font=Courier New][AB10][/font] - 10,000,000 Cr[/*]
[*][font=Courier New][AB20][/font] - 20,000,000 Cr[/*]
[*][font=Courier New][AB40][/font] - 40,000,000 Cr[/*]
[/list]

The first configured tag found in a station's name wins. Untagged stations are ignored unless [font=Courier New]Ignore tag system and handle all player stations[/font] is enabled. In that mode every operational player station is handled and its target is the station's vanilla planned budget ([font=Courier New]productionmoney[/font]).

To reproduce original HappyStation behavior, enable [font=Courier New]Ignore tag system and handle all player stations[/font], keep [font=Courier New]Top-up to fill target[/font] enabled, disable [font=Courier New]Drain surplus[/font], and set both [font=Courier New]Minimum transfer[/font] and [font=Courier New]Minimum kept player money[/font] to [font=Courier New]0[/font].

Stations under construction are also ignored until they become operational: they have no operating account yet, and the engine immediately refunds any money sent to them. Construction budgets are out of scope for this mod.

The engine quietly returns station money above the station's internal [font=Courier New]maxbudget[/font] to the player - a cap that can be tiny on warehouses regardless of the huge "expected operating budget" the UI shows. The watchdog lifts a handled station's [font=Courier New]maxbudget[/font] clear of its operating band (2x the drain trigger), so grants stick and only the watchdog's own drain reclaims surplus. Removing a tag leaves the lifted cap in place. Vanilla account-management player actions, such as changing and confirming the station account balance, will reset that internal value to the vanilla calculation under the hood.

The first check after loading a save is skipped, so the watchdog stays quiet until one full check interval has passed.

[size=4][b]Pairs well with[/b][/size]

[b]Toggle Upkeep Missions[/b] ([url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/1073]link[/url]) - its "disable money transfer missions" toggle removes the vanilla upkeep nags that demand the full calculated auto-budget, the very number this mod exists to ignore. With the watchdog managing budgets, those missions are pure noise.

